snippet.textDisplay: I have a 3-year old iPhone which is still at 100% health. I have always charged up with the ‘slow’ charger that came with phone. I keep the battery between 55-80% after visiting batteryuniversity.com and reading an article about extending the life of your battery. LION batteries hate heat so using ‘fast chargers’ really shorten the lifespan of battery. If changing phone every year it doesn’t matter how much you decrease lifespan as next owner will have to replace the battery sooner. I intend to keep the phone another 2 years hopefully so it’s imperative that I extend the lifespan of the battery as long as possible.
